[
         "sid": "50094",
         "Technique ID": "T1535",
         "Technique Name": "Phishing",
         "Quotes": ""Phishing is an attempt to acquire sensitive information such as user credentials, typically through malicious emails or websites. The rule indicates an HTTP request containing an 'img' tag that loads content from an external source (RespProxySrv), which is a common technique used in phishing emails to track user activity or deliver malicious content."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when an attempt to poison Responder is detected."
     ],
     [
         "sid": "50094",
         "Technique ID": "T1190",
         "Technique Name": "Exploit Public-Facing Application",
         "Quotes": ""Exploitation of public-facing applications is a common attack vector, especially for web servers. The rule indicates an attempt to exploit a vulnerability in a web server by sending a specially crafted HTTP request that references an external file (RespProxySrv/pictures/logo.jpg)."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when an attempt to exploit a public-facing application is detected."
     ]
 ][
     {
         "sid": "50094",
         "Technique ID": "T1190",
         "Technique Name": "Exploit Public-Facing Application",
         "Quotes": "\"Adversaries may attempt to exploit a weakness in an Internet-facing host or system to initially access a network\"",
         "Explanation": "HTTP traffic pattern indicates an attempt to exploit a web server vulnerability using a specially crafted image tag with an embedded URI to a malicious file hosted on a Responder poisoner server."
     },
     {
         "sid": "50094",
         "Technique ID": "T1490",
         "Technique Name": "Inhibit System Recovery",
         "Quotes": "\"Adversaries may delete or remove built-in data and turn off services designed to aid in the recovery of a corrupted system to prevent recovery\"",
         "Explanation": "The attack could attempt to disable system recovery mechanisms to prevent forensic analysis or system restoration."
     }
 ][
         "sid": "50094",
         "Technique ID": "T1190",
         "Technique name": "Exploit Public-Facing Application",
         "Quotes": "An adversary may attempt to exploit a weakness in an Internet-facing host or system to initially access a network.",
         "Explanation": "The rule involves an attack against a web server through an HTTP GET request that attempts to retrieve a file from a specific location. This indicates the exploitation of a vulnerability in a web application, which aligns with the T1190 technique."
     ]

         "Technique ID": "T1100",
         "Technique name": "Web Shell",
         "Quotes": ""Web Shell techniques abuse legitimate web functionality to execute arbitrary commands on a system or retrieve data"",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."

         "sid": "27967",
         "Technique ID": "T1100",
         "Technique name": "Web Shell",
         "Quotes": ""Web shells provide remote code execution and command-and-control capabilities to adversaries who have successfully compromised a web application or web server. The rule matches specific patterns in HTTP traffic associated with the Chopper web shell, indicating that the adversary is attempting to establish a remote connection to the compromised system."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."

[
         {
             "sid": "56606",
             "Technique ID": "T1105",
             "Technique name": "Ingress Tool Transfer",
             "Quotes": ""Ingress Tool Transfer techniques involve transmitting malicious tools or files into a compromised environment from a remote source. The rule indicates the presence of a variant of the CSBundleUSATodayServer RAT (Remote Access Trojan) attempting to establish communication with a command and control server. The RAT is often used to download and execute additional malicious tools or payloads, which could include keyloggers, credential stealers, or other malicious software."",
             "Explanation": "The rule has two content clauses with base64 encoded strings. Searching for the decoded strings in VirusTotal gives us results of the sample communicating with the c2 server and receiving a reverse shell payload."
         }
     ][
     "sid": "56606",
     "Technique ID": "T1005",
     "Technique name": "Data from Local System",
     "Quotes": ""Data from Local System techniques involve searching local system sources, such as file systems and configuration files or local databases, to find files of interest and sensitive data prior to Exfiltration."",
     "Explanation": "The rule detects inbound command attempts by Rat.Tool.CSBundleUSATodayServer, a malware known to exfiltrate data from compromised systems."
 ],
     "sid": "56606",
     "Technique ID": "T1105",
     "Technique name": "Ingress Tool Transfer",
     "Quotes": ""Ingress Tool Transfer technique involves transferring tools or other files from an external system into a compromised environment."",
     "Explanation": "The rule detects inbound command attempts by Rat.Tool.CSBundleUSATodayServer, which suggests the transfer of malicious tools or files into the compromised system."
 ],
     "sid": "56606",
     "Technique ID": "T1048",
     "Technique name": "Exfiltration Over Alternative Protocol",
     "Quotes": ""Exfiltration Over Alternative Protocol techniques involve stealing data by exfiltrating it over a different protocol than that of the existing command and control channel."",
     "Explanation": "The rule detects inbound command attempts by Rat.Tool.CSBundleUSATodayServer, which typically involves exfiltration of data over alternative protocols to evade detection."
 ][
         "sid": "56606",
         "Technique ID": "T1110",
         "Technique Name": "Brute Force",
         "Quotes": ""Brute force techniques involve repeatedly submitting different combinations of credentials to a system until valid credentials are found. The detection of 'RAT.Tool.CSBundleUSATodayServer' variant inbound command attempt in the rule suggests that an attacker is attempting to compromise a system by forcibly authenticating through brute force methods."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     ]

 [
         "sid": "56614",
         "Technique ID": "T1132",
         "Technique name": "Data Encoding",
         "Quotes": ""Data Encoding techniques involve encoding data to make the content of communications more difficult to detect or understand. The rule indicates the presence of a Cobalt Strike beacon connection attempt, which often uses data encoding to evade detection. Cobalt Strike is a legitimate penetration testing tool that can also be used by attackers for malicious purposes, including establishing covert communication channels with compromised systems."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     },
     {
         "sid": "56614",
         "Technique ID": "T1071",
         "Technique name": "Application Layer Protocol",
         "Quotes": ""Application Layer Protocol techniques involve using specific application layer protocols to communicate with a remote system. The rule indicates the presence of a Cobalt Strike beacon connection attempt, which typically uses the HTTP protocol to communicate with a command and control server. Cobalt Strike can use legitimate protocols to blend in with normal network traffic, making it harder to detect."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     }
 ][
         "sid": "56614",
         "Technique ID": "T1105",
         "Technique name": "Ingress Tool Transfer",
         "Quotes": ""Ingress Tool Transfer techniques involve transferring tools or other files from an external system into a compromised environment"",
         "Explanation": "The rule identifies an attempt to establish a connection to a Cobalt Strike beacon, which is a tool used by adversaries to maintain access to a compromised system."
     ],
     [
         "sid": "56614",
         "Technique ID": "T1557",
         "Technique name": "Adversary-in-the-Middle",
         "Quotes": ""Adversary-in-the-Middle (AiTM) techniques involve positioning an adversary between two or more networked devices to support follow-on behaviors"",
         "Explanation": "The rule detects communication with a Cobalt Strike beacon, which can be used to establish a reverse shell connection, enabling the adversary to act as a relay between the compromised system and the C2 server."
     ]
 ]

[
     "sid": "12372",
     "Technique ID": "T1056",
     "Technique name": "Input Capture",
     "Quotes": ""Input Capture techniques involve intercepting and capturing user input data, such as keystrokes, to obtain sensitive information. The rule specifically triggers on the presence of 'mg-shadow 2.0', which is a known keylogger tool that can intercept keystrokes and other input data. This suggests that the rule is designed to detect attempts to install or use keyloggers."",
     "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
 ][
         "sid": "12372",
         "Technique ID": "T1056",
         "Technique name": "Input Capture",
         "Quotes": ""Keyloggers are a type of malware that record keystrokes made by users, which can be used to capture sensitive information such as passwords or credit card numbers. The rule detects the presence of the 'mg-shadow 2.0' keylogger based on the detection of specific patterns in the network traffic, indicating that an attacker may be attempting to capture user input."",
         "Explanation": "This rule triggers when the mg-shadow 2.0 runtime is detected, indicating activity related to a keylogger."
     ]

[
         "sid": "59348",
         "Technique ID": "T1041",
         "Technique name": "Exfiltration Over C2 Channel",
         "Quotes": ""Exfiltration Over Command and Control Channel" techniques involve stealing data by sending it over an existing command and control channel. The rule detects an outbound connection attempt from a web shell (CWShell) that is attempting to exfiltrate information by executing commands such as "uname -a" and "Server Name:", indicating an attempt to gather system information."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     ],
     [
         "sid": "59348",
         "Technique ID": "T1003",
         "Technique name": "OS Credential Dumping",
         "Quotes": ""OS Credential Dumping" techniques involve extracting credentials, such as hashes or clear text passwords, from the operating system or software. The rule detects an outbound connection attempt from a web shell (CWShell) that is attempting to exfiltrate information by executing commands such as "uname -a" and "Server Name:", indicating an attempt to gather system information that may include credentials."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     ]
 ][
         "sid": "59348",
         "Technique ID": "T1190",
         "Technique name": "Exploit Public-Facing Application",
         "Quotes": ""Adversaries may attempt to exploit a weakness in an Internet-facing host or system to initially access a network. The rule indicates an outbound connection attempt by a web shell (CWShell) from an internal network ($HOME_NET) to an external IP address, which suggests that an adversary has exploited a vulnerability in a publicly accessible web application to gain initial access to the internal network."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     ],
     [
         "sid": "59348",
         "Technique ID": "T1003",
         "Technique name": "OS Credential Dumping",
         "Quotes": ""Adversaries may attempt to dump credentials to obtain account login and credential material, normally in the form of a hash or a clear text password, from the operating system and software. The rule indicates the presence of a web shell (CWShell) that includes functionality to execute commands on the underlying system, including the ability to dump credentials from the operating system."",
         "Explanation": "This event is generated when activity relating to malware is detected."
     ]
 ][
   {
     "sid": "59348",
     "Technique ID": "T1204",
     "Technique name": "User Execution",
     "Quotes": ""This technique relies on a user action (i.e., executing the shell command) rather than a vulnerability or exploitation method; therefore, it is not directly covered in the ATT&CK framework"",
     "Explanation": "The rule is related to PHP webshell activity, which typically involves user actions such as executing shell commands to control the compromised system."
   }
 ]
